verses.text: So they brought the ark of God , and set it in the midst of the tent that David had pitched for it: and they offered burnt sacrifices and peace offerings before God.
And when David had made an end of offering the burnt offerings and the peace offerings , he blessed the people in the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
And he dealt to every one of Israel , both man and woman , to every one a loaf of bread , and a good piece of flesh , and a flagon \add of wine\add*. \p

¶ And he appointed \add certain\add* of the Levites to minister before the ark of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, and to record , and to thank and praise the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of Israel :

Asaph the chief , and next to him Zechariah , Jeiel , and Shemiramoth , and Jehiel , and Mattithiah , and Eliab , and Benaiah , and Obed-edom : and Jeiel with psalteries and with harps ; but Asaph made a sound with cymbals ;\f + \fr 16.5 \ft with psalteries…: Heb. with instruments of psalteries and harps\f*
Benaiah also and Jahaziel the priests with trumpets continually before the ark of the covenant of God. \p
¶ Then on that day David delivered first \add this psalm\add* to thank the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* into the hand of Asaph and his brethren.
Give thanks unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, call upon his name , make known his deeds among the people.
Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him, talk ye of all his wondrous works.
Glory ye in his holy name : let the heart of them rejoice that seek the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
Seek the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* and his strength , seek his face continually.
Remember his marvellous works that he hath done , his wonders , and the judgments of his mouth ;
O ye seed of Israel his servant , ye children of Jacob , his chosen ones.
He \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God ; his judgments \add are\add* in all the earth.
Be ye mindful always of his covenant ; the word \add which\add* he commanded to a thousand generations ;
\add Even of the covenant\add* which he made with Abraham , and of his oath unto Isaac ;
And hath confirmed the same to Jacob for a law , \add and\add* to Israel \add for\add* an everlasting covenant ,
Saying , Unto thee will I give the land of Canaan , the lot of your inheritance ;\f + \fr 16.18 \ft the lot: Heb. the cord\f*
When ye were but few , even a few , and strangers in it.\f + \fr 16.19 \ft few, even: Heb. men of number, etc\f*
And \add when\add* they went from nation to nation , and from \add one\add* kingdom to another people ;
He suffered no man to do them wrong : yea, he reproved kings for their sakes,
\add Saying\add*, Touch not mine anointed , and do my prophets no harm.
Sing unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, all the earth ; shew forth from day to day his salvation.
Declare his glory among the heathen ; his marvellous works among all nations.
For great \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and greatly to be praised : he also \add is\add* to be feared above all gods.
For all the gods of the people \add are\add* idols : but the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* made the heavens.
Glory and honour \add are\add* in his presence ; strength and gladness \add are\add* in his place.

Give unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, ye kindreds of the people , give unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* glory and strength.

Give unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* the glory \add due\add* unto his name : bring an offering , and come before him: worship the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* in the beauty of holiness.
Fear before him, all the earth : the world also shall be stable , that it be not moved.
Let the heavens be glad , and let the earth rejoice : and let \add men\add* say among the nations , The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* reigneth.
Let the sea roar , and the fulness thereof: let the fields rejoice , and all that \add is\add* therein.
Then shall the trees of the wood sing out at the presence of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, because he cometh to judge the earth.
O give thanks unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; for \add he is\add* good ; for his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever.
And say ye, Save us, O God of our salvation , and gather us together , and deliver us from the heathen , that we may give thanks to thy holy name , \add and\add* glory in thy praise.

Blessed \add be\add* the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of Israel for ever and ever. And all the people said , Amen , and praised the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*. \p
¶ So he left there before the ark of the covenant of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* Asaph and his brethren , to minister before the ark continually , as every day’s work required :
And Obed-edom with their brethren , threescore and eight ; Obed-edom also the son of Jeduthun and Hosah \add to be\add* porters :
And Zadok the priest , and his brethren the priests , before the tabernacle of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in the high place that \add was\add* at Gibeon ,

To offer burnt offerings unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* upon the altar of the burnt offering continually morning and evening , and \add to do\add* according to all that is written in the law of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, which he commanded Israel ;  +  r 16.40  t morning…: Heb. in the morning, and in the evening *

And with them Heman and Jeduthun , and the rest that were chosen , who were expressed by name , to give thanks to the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, because his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever ;

And with them Heman and Jeduthun with trumpets and cymbals for those that should make a sound , and with musical instruments of God. And the sons of Jeduthun \add were\add* porters.\f + \fr 16.42 \ft porters: Heb. for the gate\f*
And all the people departed every man to his house : and David returned to bless his house.
